author: jonl
msg: Added getId() method for easy access to session id without having to retrieve the HttpSession object.  This functionality belongs in WebSession but not in Session because HTTP is a stateless protocol requiring a session id, but other Session subclasses will not necessarily have a session id concept.

msg: Added WebRequestCycle.getWebSession() for consistency and completeness and because it was useful.
